  "source_id": "pancreatic-cancer",
  "name": "Pancreatic Cancer - Comprehensive Provider Query (Multi-Resource)",
  "description": "Provider-level query identifying pancreatic cancer patients via Condition + Observation (CA 19-9). Path D captures elevated CA 19-9 without formal dx.",
  "prompt": "I need to identify my complete pancreatic cancer patient population. Some patients have a coded pancreatic cancer diagnosis. Others have only an elevated CA 19-9 tumor marker without a formal diagnosis yet — these warrant urgent imaging follow-up. Run multiple FHIR queries — diagnosis variants and CA 19-9 — and union the patient sets.",
  "prompts": {
    "naive": "Find all my pancreatic cancer patients.",
    "broad": "Find all pancreatic cancer patients — by diagnosis (malignant or carcinoma variants) or by elevated CA 19-9 (>100 U/mL). Run multiple queries and union the patient sets.",
    "expert": "Run two queries. (1) Condition?code=http://snomed.info/sct|363418001,http://snomed.info/sct|372142002 — pancreatic cancer dx variants. (2) Observation?code=http://loinc.org|24108-3&value-quantity=gt100||U/mL — elevated CA 19-9. Union the patient IDs."
  },
